\begin_layout Standard
The way Solomonoff induction works to predict sequences is that you sum
 up over all allowed computer programs — if any program is allowed, Solomonoff
 induction becomes uncomputable — with each program having a prior probability
 of (1/2) to the power of its code length in bits, and each program is further
 weighted by its fit to all data observed so far.
 This gives you a weighted mixture of experts that can predict future bits.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
